At 09:55 PM 9/7/2004 +0000, you wrote:

&gt;Dear Dr. Goodwin, Mr Johnson and group,
&gt;
&gt;I want to model ethanol hydrogasification using Cantera. I am facing
&gt;a problem because the GRI MECH 3.0 database does not include ethanol.
&gt;I am a new user of Cantera and hence need some guidance from you. It
&gt;would be of great help if you can give me some reference to related
&gt;codes.
&gt;Regards,
&gt;Gagan
&gt;
&gt;--- In cantera@yahoogroups.com, David Goodwin &lt;dgoodwin@c...&gt; wrote:
&gt; &gt; Michael,
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Cantera flags some reactions as duplicatess that Chemkin does not.
&gt;All
&gt; &gt; you have to do is tell Cantera that you intend this by adding:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; options = &quot;duplicate&quot;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; for each reaction it flags as an undeclared duplicate, for example:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; falloff_reaction( &quot;h + o2 (+ M) &lt;=&gt; ho2 (+ M)&quot;
&gt; &gt;           kf = [4.52000E+013, 0, 0],
&gt; &gt;           kf0   = [1.05000E+019, -1.257, 0],
&gt; &gt;           efficiencies = &quot; ch4:10  co:1.9  co2:3.8  h2:0  h2o:0
&gt;n2:0 &quot;,
&gt; &gt;           options = &quot;duplicate&quot;)
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; This is done intentionallly, since a reaction like h + o2 (+ n2)
&gt;&lt;=&gt;
&gt; &gt; ho2 (+ n2) could also be written as h + o2 (+ M) &lt;=&gt; ho2 (+ M) with
&gt;all
&gt; &gt; efficiencies set to zero except the one for n2.
&gt; &gt; Also, if you have two reactions
&gt; &gt;   A + B &lt;=&gt; C + D
&gt; &gt; and
&gt; &gt; C + D &lt;=&gt; A + B
&gt; &gt; Cantera says these are duplicates, but Chemkin does not.
&gt; &gt; Cantera performs some other checks too, such as whether NASA
&gt;polynomial
&gt; &gt; thermo parameterizations are continuous at the midpoint
&gt;temperature,
&gt; &gt; etc.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; These extra checks can help find error in reaction mechanisms that
&gt; &gt; might otherwise go unnoticed, which is especially a problem with
&gt;very
&gt; &gt; large mechanisms.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Dave
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; On Aug 6, 2004, at 9:15 AM, Michael Johnson wrote:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Dear Dave and group,
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; I am trying to use the ethanol mechanism of Marinov, available at:
&gt; &gt; &gt; www-cms.llnl.gov/combustion/combustion2.html
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; ck2cti converts it to cti format with no problem, but there are
&gt; &gt; &gt; three-body
&gt; &gt; &gt; falloff reactions that have different low-pressure coefficients
&gt;for
&gt; &gt; &gt; different third bodies and Cantera has problems with that.
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; The reactions are:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; #  Reaction 4
&gt; &gt; &gt; falloff_reaction( &quot;h + o2 (+ M) &lt;=&gt; ho2 (+ M)&quot;,
&gt; &gt; &gt;          kf = [4.52000E+013, 0, 0],
&gt; &gt; &gt;          kf0   = [1.05000E+019, -1.257, 0],
&gt; &gt; &gt;          efficiencies = &quot; ch4:10  co:1.9  co2:3.8  h2:0  h2o:0
&gt;n2:0 &quot;)
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; #  Reaction 5
&gt; &gt; &gt; falloff_reaction( &quot;h + o2 (+ n2) &lt;=&gt; ho2 (+ n2)&quot;,
&gt; &gt; &gt;          kf = [4.52000E+013, 0, 0],
&gt; &gt; &gt;          kf0   = [2.03000E+020, -1.59, 0])
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; (and two others with n2 and h2o as third bodies)
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; The error I get with Cantera is:
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Procedure: installReaction
&gt; &gt; &gt; Error:   Undeclared duplicate reactions detected:
&gt; &gt; &gt; Reaction 4: h + o2 (+ M) &lt;=&gt; ho2 (+ M)
&gt; &gt; &gt; Reaction 5: h + o2 (+ n2) &lt;=&gt; ho2 (+ n2)
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; What can be done in this situation?
&gt; &gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; &gt; Thanks,
&gt; &gt; &gt; Michael
